  "texts": [
    "The medium is assumed to be in equilibrium.",
    "• Temperature dependence of heavy quark masses The temperature dependence of quark mass is taken asm 0 + V ∞ (T)/2, where m 0 is the bare mass -taken as 1.47 GeV for c quarks and 4.88 GeV for b quarks and V ∞ is the asymptotic value of the 1D real potential.",
    "• Equilibrium limits in transport The QME (5) admits a unique asymptotic state for each temperature and such a state is reached as the final outcome of any initial state.",
    "For large relative distance, the complex potential saturates and the QME for the Q Q pair splits into two independent QMEs for each quark.",
    "In the semi-classical limit, these QMEs are equivalent to Fokker-Planck equations (with a momentum diffusion coefficient expressed as W (0)) and naturally lead to Boltzmann distributions for individual quarks."
  ],
